      "content": "Talking to a pharmacist immediately about your specific concerns is actually the fastest safe route to get help with stress and medications, as they are legally trained to give you guidance on over-the-counter safety. While many vitamins and herbs interact with serotonin, people with mild anxiety sometimes find temporary relief from OTC options like L-theanine or magnesium, but you must confirm this with a pharmacist to be absolutely sure before taking them. Please avoid self-treating with new supplements until you have verified safety, as they may not help and could still cause an interaction. Using non-drug tools like brief breathing exercises and adequate sleep might also help you get through finals safely without risking your health.",
